e with limited exceptions (as per the rule's allowance for exceptions).\n- This is supported by the court's own referenced example (April 2024 closure).\n- Evidence from credible reports confirms the non-weather context and official source.\n\nSo, I called aar_submit_council_vote with vote: demonstrated and a short rationale. The response was \"Council vote accepted.\" Now, the next step is to report back that the vote was accepted and stop. Since the response included \"ok: true\" and \"Council vote accepted.\", the task is complete.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":"","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1781914326-uUYDO1NJQdXmuUmzae9A","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781914326456,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":20656,"output":651,"totalTokens":21307}},"type":"message_update"}
